Accountting Assistant Manager - PT Alcar Chemco Indonesia
Accountting Assistant Manager  -
Accountting Assistant Manager
Responsibilities
Develop and manage Finance, Accounting & Tax Department Budget to ensure department program and activities are executed in accordance with the plan and support the achievement of Company’s goals and objectivesMaintain internal control and safeguards for receipt of revenue, costs, and program budgets and actual expendituresConsistently analyze financial data and present financial reports in accurate and timely manner,; and monitor progress the Company’s financial statusAssist in the annual budgeting and planning process, administer and review all financial plans and compare to actual results with a view to identify, explain, and correct variances as appropriateProactive analysis of variances and communication of issues and opportunities to operations managementReview capital expenditures and side expenses to ensure the correctness and in-line with the approved budgetSupport Finance Head with special projects and workflow process improvement.People management – Lead and manage subordinates effectively  Requirements :Maximum age 35 years oldGraduated minimum S-1 Accounting from reputable universityAt least 3 years working experience as Finance, Accounting, TaxHaving knowledge in standard accounting policy and guidelineHaving experience in related of Financial report (BS, PL, Cash Flow), cost control, general accounting, reporting, and general ledger.Strong leadership, positive working attitude, good initiative and willing to learnExcellent problem solving and analytical skill, accurate in detail, able to work under pressureStrong interpersonal and communication skills; experience in effectively communicating key data, including presentation to senior managementFamiliar with Microsoft office software: word, excel, power point, internet, accounting software.Able to speak English is must.Physically and mentally healthy
